╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║  HELIX TRAINER — Exercise 2.2: Extend Mode                      ║
║  Category: Selection             Difficulty: ★☆☆ Fundamental    ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

COMMANDS TO LEARN
─────────────────
  v       Enter select (extend) mode
  v       Press again to exit back to normal mode
  Esc     Also exits select mode

In select mode, ALL motions EXTEND the selection instead of
replacing it. This is like Vim's visual mode but integrated
into Helix's selection-first model.

INSTRUCTIONS
────────────
  Each line has a phrase enclosed in << >> markers.
  Select from << to >> (inclusive) using extend mode, then delete.

  Strategy:
  1. Position cursor on the first <
  2. Press v to enter extend mode
  3. Use f > then ; or just l repeatedly to reach past >>
  4. Press d to delete

  The result should have no << >> markers or their contents.

────────────────────────── PRACTICE ──────────────────────────────

Hello <<remove this>> world.
The <<delete me>> quick brown fox.
Coding <<not this part>> is fun.
Helix <<or this>> is great.

────────────────────────── EXPECTED ──────────────────────────────

Hello  world.
The  quick brown fox.
Coding  is fun.
Helix  is great.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
HINTS (read only if stuck):
  Hint 1: Move to <, press v, then f > to jump to the first >.
          But you need to include the second > too.
  Hint 2: After f >, press l to extend one more character to
          include the closing >, then d.
  Hint 3: Alternative: f < to land on first <, then v f > l d.
  Hint 4: Another approach: use / to search for <<.*?>> pattern,
          but that's a more advanced technique.
